-- China Stocks: Beiqi Foton, Huaneng Power, Sinopec, Vanke
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-16T07:51:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-15/china-southern-airlines-co-icbc-saic-motor-vanke-china-equity-preview.html
The  Shanghai Composite Index , which
tracks the bigger of China’s stock exchanges, fell 4 percent to
2,894.54. The  CSI 300 Index  dropped 4.4 percent to 3,169.54.  Property developers: China ordered first-time foreign
homebuyers to show proof they don’t own other properties in the
country as it steps up measures to curb gains in the real estate
market, the housing ministry and currency regulator said.  China Vanke Co.  (000002 CH), the nation’s largest developer
by market value, fell 4.3 percent to 8.16 yuan.  Poly Real Estate
Group Co.  (600048 CH), the second-biggest developer, dropped 5.5
percent to 12.24 yuan.  Utility and oil companies: China’s utility companies and
oil refiners are among the “most susceptible” to government
policies to contain inflation, according to Credit Suisse Group
AG.  Huaneng Power Intl Inc  (600011 CH) declined 2.3 percent to
6.02 yuan.  China Petroleum & Chemical Corp.  (600028 CH) fell 5.3
percent to 8.46 yuan.  Beiqi Foton Motor Co.  (600166 CH): The automaker said its
October sales fell to 50,364 units from 50,583 a year earlier.
For the first 10 months, sales gained 15 percent to 571,115. The
stock slid 5.1 percent to 22.93 yuan.  -- Irene Shen  in Shanghai. Editors:  Allen Wan , Richard Frost  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
